<bug>
    <id>9058</id>
    <title>docker run --device does not preserve group</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">The "docker run" command flag "device" does not preserve the localhost device group when copied into the docker container.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">```
docker run --device=/dev/snd/timer:/dev/snd/timer -p 2222:22 -dt sound/example</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1"># On my local system
[localhost]$ ls -l /dev/snd/timer
crw-rw----+ 1 root audio 116, 33 Oct 25 23:16 /dev/snd/timer</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1"># Inside the docker instance
[user@2ecae939d223 ~]$ ls -l /dev/snd/timer
crw-rw----.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">1 root root 116, 33 Nov 10 00:52 /dev/snd/timer
```</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
